&lt;Worldwide 800 Services Inc>,whose Service 800 unit recently filed a lawsuit againstAmerican Telephone and Telegraph Co for false advertising andanti-competitive practices, said it has named &lt;Young andRubicam>, an advertising firm, as a defendent in the case.    Worldwide said Young and Rubicam designed and placed theATT advertisements in question.    The amended complaint, filed in the U.S. District Court forthe Northern District of Illinois Eastern Division, seeksinjuctive relief damages, the company said.    The suit charges Young and Rubicam with misrepresentingATT's involvement in the toll-free international dialingservice network through a series of false and misleadingadvertisements. Reuter&#3;